  "chapter": 7,
  "section": 8,
  "book": "algebra-1",
  "epigraph": {
    "text": "His master replied, `Well done, good and faithful \nservant! You have been faithful with a few things; I will put you in \ncharge of many things.'",
    "reference": "Matthew 25:21",
    "quote": "An expert is a person who has made all the mistakes that can be made in a very narrow field.",
    "quoteAuthor": "Niels Bohr"
  },
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "{An expert is a person who has made all the mistakes that can be made in a very narrow field.}{Niels Bohr}"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "This chapter has built your fluency with exponents and polynomials. \nThe exponent rules you've learned will appear throughout your \nmathematical journey, and polynomial operations form the foundation \nfor the factoring techniques in the next chapter."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Key Concepts Summary"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Vocabulary Review"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "Exponent A. Expression with one term",
        "Base B. The number being raised to a power",
        "Coefficient C. Polynomial with three terms",
        "Polynomial D. Number multiplying a variable",
        "Monomial E. Highest power in a polynomial",
        "Binomial F. Power to which a base is raised",
        "Trinomial G. Expression with two terms",
        "Degree H. Sum of terms with non-negative integer exponents"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "*Answers: 1-F, 2-B, 3-D, 4-H, 5-A, 6-G, 7-C, 8-E*"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Chapter Review Exercises"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "**Exponent Rules (Sections 7.1–7.2)**"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "$x^4 \\cdot x^7$",
        "$\\dfrac{a^9}{a^3}$",
        "$(y^5)^3$",
        "$(3x^2)^4$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Write with positive exponents."
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "$x^{-3}$",
        "$\\dfrac{a^{-2}}{b^{-4}}$",
        "$(2x^{-1}y^2)^{-3}$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "$5^0 + 5^{-1}$",
        "$\\left(\\frac{2}{3}\\right)^{-2}$",
        "$4^{-2} \\cdot 4^3$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "**Scientific Notation (Section 7.3)**"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Write in scientific notation."
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "$47,000,000$",
        "$0.000065$",
        "$8,200$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Compute and write in scientific notation."
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "$(3 \\times 10^4)(4 \\times 10^5)$",
        "$\\dfrac{8.4 \\times 10^{-2}}{2.1 \\times 10^3}$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "**Polynomials (Sections 7.4–7.7)**"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Identify the degree and leading coefficient."
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "$5x^3 - 2x^2 + x - 4$",
        "$7 - 3x + x^4$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Add or subtract."
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "$(3x^2 + 5x - 2) + (x^2 - 3x + 4)$",
        "$(5a^2 - 4a + 1) - (2a^2 + 3a - 5)$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "$-2x(3x^2 - 4x + 5)$",
        "$(x + 3)(x - 7)$",
        "$(2x - 5)(3x + 4)$",
        "$(x + 2)(x^2 - 2x + 4)$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Use special products."
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "$(x + 8)^2$",
        "$(3x - 2)^2$",
        "$(4a + 5)(4a - 5)$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Mixed Review"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Simplify completely."
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": true,
      "items": [
        "$\\dfrac{(x^3y^{-2})^2}{(x^{-1}y^4)^{-1}}$",
        "$(a^2 - 3a + 1) + (2a^2 + a - 4) - (a^2 - 2a + 3)$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "If $f(x) = x^2 - 4x + 3$, find $f(x + h) - f(x)$."
    }
  ]
}